    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (76.05) is our clear centerpiece, benefiting from a favorable matchup against Cameron (L) that minimizes his usual platoon regression and maximizes his high base floor. We are also leaning heavily into **Jonathan Aranda** (68.94) and **Yainer Diaz** (66.01) to provide the bulk of our offensive production. **Jonathan Aranda** is a standout play because of his 19% SP skill advantage against Assad, while **Yainer Diaz** gains a significant park factor boost, helping to mitigate the efficiency drag of batting in the bottom third of the order. Meanwhile, **Lawrence Butler** (62.58) provides high-upside value; his massive 13% dynamic platoon edge against Schlittler makes him our premier value play in the outfield, even with a moderate SP matchup.\n\nRegarding our bench decisions, **Cal Raleigh** (46.77) was the most difficult exclusion from the starting lineup. While his underlying xwOBA remains strong, the brutal matchup against Eovaldi\u2019s 3.17 xERA triggered a significant SP-skill penalty that pushed him just below the threshold required to displace our current starters. We are also proceeding with caution regarding **Bryson Stott** (50.24) and **Yainer Diaz**; both rely on projected lineup spots that have not yet been confirmed. **Bryson Stott** specifically carries elevated risk, as a potential move down the order combined with the difficulty of facing Ray (L) leaves him in a precarious \"marginal\" state. **Daulton Varsho** and **Masyn Winn** are active, but they face high-difficulty pitchers in Yamamoto and Cavalli, respectively, so we will be monitoring their early at-bats closely to ensure our daily game caps are not wasted on low-ceiling outings.",
